<item>
            <title>[LU-9800] recovery-mds-scale test_failover_mds: test_failover_mds returned 1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9800</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/55045e59-2766-4676-91ae-45a2fa2f4e91&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/55045e59-2766-4676-91ae-45a2fa2f4e91&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The dd client loads for test_failover_mds and test_failover_ost are running out of space.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This looks different than &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5788&quot; title=&quot;recovery-double-scale test_pairwise_fail: no enough free disk space&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5788&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5788&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; because the recovery-mds subtests ran for 22 hours.  The&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5788&quot; title=&quot;recovery-double-scale test_pairwise_fail: no enough free disk space&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5788&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5788&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; failures normally happened in less than a minute.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From both test_logs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Client load failed 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From both run_dd_debug logs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;dd: error writing &#8216;/mnt/lustre/d0.dd-trevis-49vm5.trevis.hpdd.intel.com/dd-file&#8217;: No space left on device
964211+0 records in
964210+0 records out
+ &apos;[&apos; 1 -eq 0 &apos;]&apos;
2017-07-11 23:55:13: dd failed
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>trevis, failover&lt;br/&gt;
server: EL7, zfs, branch master, v2.10.50.3, b3612 &lt;br/&gt;
client: EL7, branch master, v2.10.50.3, b3612&lt;br/&gt;
</environment>
